
[1]offensively

   OFFENS'IVELY, adv.

   1. In a manner to give displeasure; as language offensively harsh or
   sarcastic.

   2. Injuriously; mischievously.

   3. By way of invasion or first attack. The enemy was not in a condition
   to act offensively.

   4. Unpleasantly to the senses.
